# CODEOWNERS — Colorado Environmental Data Hub
#
# Maps repository paths to the roles responsible for reviewing them, so review
# responsibility is legible and every part of the project has an owner. GitHub
# requests a review from the listed owners when a PR touches a matching path.
#
# Today the project is single-maintainer, so @brianckeegan owns everything; the
# inline comments record which ROLES.md role *should* take each path over as the
# undergraduate team and CEJ partnership are onboarded. Replace @brianckeegan
# with team handles (e.g. @CUPIDS-Lab/data-engineers) once those teams exist.
# Later entries win, so order is general -> specific.

# Default owner: the project manager catches anything not matched below.
*                           @brianckeegan

# Data lives with the data engineer: the immutable source catalog, schema.
/data/                      @brianckeegan
/docs/reference/DATA-DICTIONARY.md   @brianckeegan   # -> subject-matter expert

# Liberation pipelines are the engineer's + developer's shared ground.
/pipelines/                 @brianckeegan   # -> data-engineer + software-developer

# Design memos carry the research methodology: SME / methodology owner.
/context/                   @brianckeegan   # -> subject-matter expert

# Governance, charter, roles set the project's terms: project manager owns them,
# with legal as a second reviewer on the terms that bind partners + privacy.
/docs/governance/GOVERNANCE.md              @brianckeegan   # -> project-manager + legal
/docs/governance/CHARTER.md                 @brianckeegan   # -> project-manager
/docs/governance/ROLES.md                   @brianckeegan   # -> project-manager
/docs/governance/collaboration-protocol.md  @brianckeegan   # -> project-manager
/docs/governance/contributed-data-intake.md @brianckeegan   # -> data-engineer + legal

# Responsible-data, DMP, and the QA checklists gate sensitive + published work.
/docs/responsible-data/responsible-data-checklist.md    @brianckeegan   # -> project-manager + legal
/docs/responsible-data/data-management-plan.md          @brianckeegan   # -> project-manager
/docs/responsible-data/INSTALLED-BASE.md                @brianckeegan   # -> project-manager
/docs/responsible-data/data-bulletproofing-checklist.md @brianckeegan   # -> data-engineer + statistics
/docs/responsible-data/data-quality-checklist.md        @brianckeegan   # -> data-engineer
/docs/responsible-data/accessibility-checklist.md       @brianckeegan   # -> communicators
/docs/responsible-data/data-card.md                     @brianckeegan   # -> subject-matter expert

# CI, automation, and the nested guidance skills affect everyone's
# reproducibility -> the software developer keeps them in sync.
/.github/                   @brianckeegan   # -> software-developer
/.skills/                   @brianckeegan   # -> software-developer
